edu.dhbw.t10.manager.output
Class Output

java.lang.Object
  edu.dhbw.t10.manager.output.Output

public class Output
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides the functionallity of printing Strings via sending Key Strokes to the system.
Letters, big letters and numbers are converted directly to their own java.awt.event.KeyEvent constant, which is sent.
All other symbols are written via their Unicode.
Control symbols are sent via their java.awt.event.KeyEvent constant

Author:
DanielAl

printString

protected boolean printString(java.lang.String charSequence,
                              int type)
Switch with type over different sendKey calls.
- Key.CONTROL is used for Control Symbols like Enter or Space.
- Key.UNICODE is used for a Unicode Sequence.
- Key.CHAR is used for normal chars.
- Key.UNKNOWN produces a logger warning.
The Key.CHAR type differntiate between Big, Small an Unicode Letters...
Converts a char with convertKeyCode to a Key.Constant

Parameters:
String - charSequence, int type
Returns:
boolean

printCombi

protected boolean printCombi(java.util.ArrayList<Key> hold,
                             java.util.ArrayList<Key> press)
Prints a combi by calling for each Key Element of the ArrayList the sendKey with function COMBI.
Now press Keys while the others are hold.
When the List is empty, call the special mode of the COMBI Branch of sendKey to release all pressed Keys...

Parameters:
hold - ArrayList set all Keys which have to be hold during the Combi
press - ArrayList set all Keys which have to be pressed during the Combi
Returns:
boolean

convertKeyCode

private java.lang.Integer convertKeyCode(java.lang.String code,
                                         int type)
Converts a Stringcode into a Constant of the KeyEvent class via Reflection.
These constants could be used for sending Keys.
The type parameter is for differentiate a number to be a normal Keynumber oder a NUMPAD Number.

Exceptions SecurityException, NoSuchFieldException,IllegalArgumentException, IllegalAccessException which are thrown by reflection returned the KeyEvent.UNKNOWN

Parameters:
String - code, int type
Returns:
Integer

sendUnicode

private boolean sendUnicode(java.lang.String uni)
Sends a Unicode in the Format \U+XXXX\ to the System by using a System specific Key combination.
Windows and Linux are supported.
For Windows compability a Registry hack is necessary. Use the install.reg to enable HexaDecimal Unicode Input in Windows and restart your System.
Implemented directly with a sequence of sendKey() methods and not with the printCombi function Mac support untested...

Parameters:
String - uni
Returns:
boolean

sendKey

private boolean sendKey(int key,
                        int function)
Send Key Codes to the System with a Robot and java.awt.event.KeyEvent constants.
Functions:
- PRESS for type a Key
- HOLD for pressing and holding a key
- RELEASE for releasing a key
- COMBI for Key COmbination functionallity; used in printCombi()
- SHIFT for shift a Key to its Uppercase and type it...
Hint: keyPress('ö') tested and it don't work

Parameters:
int - key, int function
Returns:
boolean
